24:57.390 --> 24:58.910
Well, who authorized that?

25:01.120 --> 25:01.990
You're kidding me.

25:02.060 --> 25:05.080
- Look, Sarah, I can explain...
- No, I will talk to her. Thank you.

25:05.870 --> 25:07.270
Mom, what the hell are you doing?

25:07.440 --> 25:10.060
Look, it's worth the time
and effort. I know it.

25:10.130 --> 25:12.060
So you paid for more drilling?

25:12.100 --> 25:14.420
- It's my money.
- There's nothing there, mom.

25:14.460 --> 25:16.030
If there was, they
would've found it by now.

25:16.100 --> 25:18.250
Sarah, it's just a few more days drilling.

25:18.290 --> 25:20.090
Oh, God, mom. I love
you, but you have to stop.

25:20.140 --> 25:22.470
You cannot solve everybody's problems...

25:22.560 --> 25:24.360
mine, Kitty's, Saul's.

25:24.410 --> 25:26.420
- Just leave it alone.
- No, I don't believe, as a family,

25:26.460 --> 25:29.660
- we can't help each other.
- Then how can I move on if you don't?

25:35.850 --> 25:37.260
I need more information, Robert.

25:37.300 --> 25:39.070
I'm starting to feel
really weird about this.

25:39.210 --> 25:40.840
There's nothing more I can say.

25:42.280 --> 25:43.670
Why are you taking amiodarone?

25:45.940 --> 25:47.730
I started to have some arrhythmia again.

25:49.540 --> 25:50.330
Does Kitty know?

25:50.370 --> 25:51.750
- I didn't think anyone knew.
- I'm sorry.

25:51.780 --> 25:53.550
I saw the bottle on your desk, all right?

25:53.580 --> 25:55.290
And now you're telling me
you're hiding it from Kitty.

25:55.340 --> 25:56.600
- What is going on, Robert?
- What I'm

25:56.630 --> 25:58.600
asking you to do has
nothing to do with my health.

25:58.640 --> 26:00.740
- Then what is in the safety deposit box?
- Justin, don't do this.

26:00.780 --> 26:02.810
- I need to. You can't expect me to just...
- No, I can expect it.

26:02.830 --> 26:05.050
That's why I chose you.
That's the whole point.

26:06.060 --> 26:08.480
I'm sorry. I'm worried about you, Robert.

26:10.090 --> 26:11.260
Give me the key back.

26:11.860 --> 26:13.900
I mean it. I clearly
chose the wrong person.

26:15.270 --> 26:17.060
Hey, guys. Tasting menu's ready.

26:18.240 --> 26:19.140
Excuse me.

26:23.880 --> 26:26.090
Is he okay? 'Cause he
seems a little testy.

26:26.190 --> 26:28.400
Yeah, you know what?
He... he's fine. He's fine.

26:31.320 --> 26:32.640
Uncle Saul, I... I'm...

26:33.200 --> 26:34.450
Sorry. I didn't realize...

26:34.480 --> 26:36.810
It's okay. Come on. Let's go eat.

26:45.200 --> 26:46.400
Menus.

26:46.570 --> 26:48.220
Thank you. Menus.

26:54.770 --> 26:55.390
Thank you.

26:55.470 --> 26:56.740
Menus.

26:57.250 --> 27:01.070
Okay, so, uh, the idea
behind our restaurant

27:01.150 --> 27:03.910
is comfort food meets organic meets tapas.

27:03.990 --> 27:06.170
And we are very hopeful
and very optimistic.

27:06.500 --> 27:08.040
We better be, 'cause we open in a month.

27:08.340 --> 27:10.220
So, um, you all have your menus.

27:10.300 --> 27:12.040
Um, mark down what you
like in order of preference.

27:12.090 --> 27:14.080
And I want everybody's
opinion, not just Kevin's.

27:15.300 --> 27:16.840
- So, uh, dig in.
- You all right?

27:16.880 --> 27:19.760
What's wrong? Robert?

27:20.070 --> 27:22.060
- I think someone should call 911.
- What's wrong?

27:22.110 --> 27:24.110
- Robert. Robert.
- Justin!

27:24.220 --> 27:25.980
- Call 911.
- What's happening?

27:26.030 --> 27:27.910
You okay? You okay? It's all right.

27:27.950 --> 27:29.940
Look at me. Breathe.
Just breathe, all right?

27:47.320 --> 27:48.730
Oh, hey.

27:49.210 --> 27:51.400
- Oh, wow. What time is it?
- It's early.

27:53.020 --> 27:54.040
How are you feeling?

27:54.490 --> 27:56.560
I've been watching you.
What could be better?

27:56.810 --> 27:59.200
Hmm. I need coffee.

27:59.260 --> 28:00.800
I will call room service.

28:06.140 --> 28:07.100
You know what, honey?

28:09.380 --> 28:10.410
It's not funny.

28:11.160 --> 28:13.410
You have been walking
around with an arrhythmia,

28:13.450 --> 28:14.930
and you never bothered to tell me.

28:16.530 --> 28:17.540
I didn't want you to...

28:17.620 --> 28:19.050
Didn't... didn't want what?

28:19.110 --> 28:21.980
I... to have to choose
between me and the campaign.

28:22.370 --> 28:23.700
That's what grown-ups do.

28:24.520 --> 28:27.370
We talk about it and we set priorities.

28:27.420 --> 28:30.310
- But I want you to win.
- Robert, we had to call an ambulance.

28:33.520 --> 28:34.390
Look...

28:35.240 --> 28:36.610
I got dizzy, all right?

28:37.130 --> 28:38.370
I shouldn't have said anything.

28:38.420 --> 28:40.180
You are... I... I'm sorry.

28:40.270 --> 28:42.450
- Seriously, you are unbelievable.
- I'm... I'm... I'm sorry.

28:42.490 --> 28:43.810
You know that? You are unbelievable.

28:45.960 --> 28:48.960
You just will never accept
anything from anyone.

28:49.810 --> 28:52.680
You are incredibly stoic, and I...

28:55.660 --> 28:58.160
I love that about you.

28:59.090 --> 28:59.850
I really do.

28:59.900 --> 29:04.150
But, you know, I also love the
part of you that is vulnerable.

29:04.200 --> 29:06.640
I love the part of you that needs me.

29:07.410 --> 29:10.700
When you can't figure out what
tie to wear, I am in heaven.

29:10.830 --> 29:12.280
When you can't find your glasses, I...

29:12.340 --> 29:13.470
forget about it. I'm...

29:15.000 --> 29:18.120
I just didn't fall in love with the hero.

29:19.090 --> 29:22.420
I fell in love with the guy who was
afraid that, after his heart attack...

29:23.700 --> 29:26.500
he wasn't gonna be able
to keep up with his kid.

29:34.020 --> 29:34.680
Look...

29:36.310 --> 29:38.800
I may have gotten myself into a situation.

29:41.190 --> 29:42.580
Those hits that you've been taking?

29:43.500 --> 29:44.710
They're directed at me.

29:45.880 --> 29:48.540
They're shots across the
bow from a guy named Stanton.

29:49.370 --> 29:51.790
He's in line for a big defense contract.

29:54.460 --> 29:55.320
Go on.

30:01.570 --> 30:02.460
You're out early.

30:02.510 --> 30:05.100
Yeah. I went for a little walk.

30:06.770 --> 30:08.380
- I just talked to Kitty.
- Oh?

30:08.420 --> 30:10.150
She said Robert's gonna be all right.

30:10.210 --> 30:12.770
They are releasing him
from the hospital today.

30:12.850 --> 30:15.080
Oh, boy. That's great. Thank God, huh?

30:16.240 --> 30:18.080
- You're the one I'm worried about.
- Me?

30:18.310 --> 30:20.900
Yeah. Oh, I see. You've
been talking to the boys.

30:22.160 --> 30:25.170
I'm so sorry I didn't know
what you were going through.

30:25.590 --> 30:28.000
Please tell me about this friend of yours.

30:29.980 --> 30:30.790
What can I say?

30:30.840 --> 30:32.210
He wasn't the only one.

30:34.260 --> 30:35.210
I... I... I...

30:37.150 --> 30:39.600
I spent most of my life
living in shame, Nora.

30:39.640 --> 30:42.380
There were no role models
for me when I was growing up.

30:42.850 --> 30:44.250
But you can't be alone every night,

30:44.300 --> 30:46.280
and there... there were
times when I let myself...

30:46.360 --> 30:47.730
but it was always in secret,

30:48.490 --> 30:50.320
and it was rarely with the same person,

30:50.380 --> 30:52.850
so it could never be anything real.

30:53.500 --> 30:54.940
I made sure of that.

30:55.410 --> 30:58.660
Didn't you worry about
what that might cost you?

30:58.710 --> 31:00.490
Don't forget. We knew nothing
about what was going on

31:00.520 --> 31:01.750
in those days, and there were

31:01.790 --> 31:04.860
- times...
- I meant cost you... your... your heart, your soul.

31:05.620 --> 31:09.100
No. No, I c... I couldn't
let myself think that way.

31:09.160 --> 31:10.400
Well, then it's time to start.

31:10.620 --> 31:12.330
Your life is not over yet.

31:12.450 --> 31:14.510
W... when do you get your results?

31:15.190 --> 31:16.910
Now. Today. Whenever I want.

31:16.990 --> 31:19.220
Good. Let's call, and I'll
sit right here with you.

31:19.270 --> 31:21.130
No, I have to do that
when I'm alone. Please.

31:21.200 --> 31:23.960
For crying out loud, what
is wrong with everyone?

31:24.010 --> 31:26.680
What, is there a moratorium
on compassion around here?

31:26.820 --> 31:30.190
We're family. That means you
don't have to do things alone.

31:30.280 --> 31:31.210
That's the whole point.

31:31.280 --> 31:32.410
You are so pushy.

31:32.470 --> 31:33.880
Well, tough.

31:35.540 --> 31:36.740
Here. Take that.

31:36.870 --> 31:37.590
All right.

31:37.940 --> 31:38.930
I have to get the number.

31:39.910 --> 31:41.840
All right. Here it is.

31:48.600 --> 31:51.060
I had a test the other day.
I'm calling for the results.

31:52.090 --> 31:53.310
Saul Holden.

31:53.820 --> 31:55.060
H-o-l-d-e-n.

31:55.560 --> 31:58.420
My birthday is August 11, 1938.

32:02.270 --> 32:03.050
Thank you.

32:03.860 --> 32:04.820
Yeah, thank you.

32:06.920 --> 32:07.750
I'm fine.

32:08.950 --> 32:09.820
I'm fine.

32:10.660 --> 32:13.080
Mom, Holly called. We gotta go.

32:13.130 --> 32:14.720
- Where?
- Narrow Lake. Hurry!

32:15.140 --> 32:17.770
Come on. Narrow Lake.

32:21.780 --> 32:23.510
Can you believe this?

32:23.570 --> 32:25.540
- What is it?
- It's an aquifer.

32:25.590 --> 32:27.520
It's our aquifer.

32:27.570 --> 32:30.250
It's Narrow Lake! I knew it! I knew it!

32:30.300 --> 32:31.470
What does this mean exactly?

32:31.500 --> 32:34.440
It means that we are
in the water business.

32:34.480 --> 32:38.280
I mean, do you know how
much California needs water?

32:38.350 --> 32:41.480
- We are going to be rich?
- How deep is it?

32:41.530 --> 32:43.880
They said it's the deepest
one they've ever seen.

32:43.930 --> 32:45.820
Well, tell 'em to stop
it. Boys, turn it off.

32:45.860 --> 32:47.620
They're getting a well cap. Don't worry.

32:47.640 --> 32:49.410
Oh, dear. We don't want it to run out.

32:49.560 --> 32:53.480
Nora, it's enormous. It's
an entire ocean under there.

32:53.560 --> 32:54.690
What are you doing?

32:55.820 --> 32:56.730
What are you doing?

32:56.760 --> 32:58.540
Oh, no!

33:00.510 --> 33:02.740
Okay, come on, Nora. Let's go.

33:25.130 --> 33:26.370
Yeah sure, right.

33:26.580 --> 33:28.340
I guess I wasn't feeling so hot.

33:28.810 --> 33:30.060
You still want me to give you the key back?

33:30.110 --> 33:32.360
Actually, I do, but not
because I don't trust you.

33:32.600 --> 33:35.060
I think Kitty and I should
handle this ourselves.

33:35.110 --> 33:36.639
Oh, you told Kitty. That's good.

33:36.640 --> 33:39.960
Yeah, I told her everything.

33:37.990 --> 33:39.960
I probably should've a long
time ago, but I think I...

33:40.540 --> 33:42.750
Have to keep learning
this lesson over and over.

33:42.890 --> 33:46.280
Hey. So I heard you were part of a
very covert operation this weekend.

33:46.340 --> 33:48.970
Uh, yeah. So covert, I had
no idea what was going on.

33:49.090 --> 33:51.180
All right. Well, I guess I'll see you guys

33:51.210 --> 33:53.390
- back at the bat cave.
- All right, Justin. Take care.

33:56.060 --> 33:57.520
- Bye.
- See you later, boo-boo. Take care.

33:57.580 --> 33:58.930
- Bye, darling.
- I love you.

34:01.250 --> 34:04.300
Sarah, I know how much you
like the chipotle meat loaf.

34:04.740 --> 34:05.750
Thank you.

34:06.090 --> 34:07.940
You know, your restaurant's
gonna be a big hit.

34:08.110 --> 34:09.020
- Thank you.
- And if not,

34:09.080 --> 34:10.830
Sarah can support you
for the rest of your life

34:10.870 --> 34:13.020
now that she and mom are
the water queens of Ojai.

34:13.050 --> 34:16.060
I think there's enough
queens in the family.

34:16.239 --> 34:17.550
- Oh, Nora.
- Yes.

34:17.690 --> 34:20.560
- Here. This is the Mac and cheese.
- Oh, Scotty. Thank you.

34:20.600 --> 34:21.449
- Come on.
- Okay.

34:21.489 --> 34:23.080
- Bye. Bye.
- Mom...

34:23.139 --> 34:26.290
- Yeah.
- Even if we hadn't found water, I wouldn't trade

34:26.320 --> 34:29.940
- that miserable bus trip for all the pizza in the world.
- You know what?

34:29.989 --> 34:31.199
She's going out again next

34:31.239 --> 34:33.300
- weekend to the bay area.
- Don't push your luck.

34:33.330 --> 34:34.489
- It's wine country.
- Get in the car.

34:34.520 --> 34:36.909
- All right, I'm getting in the car. I'm getting in the car.
- Bye!

34:36.980 --> 34:37.770
Okay, let's go. Hit the road.

34:37.840 --> 34:41.310
- Bye, guys. Bye...
- Oh, you angel. Bye.

34:41.360 --> 34:43.190
Oh, thank you. Bye, you guys.

34:43.230 --> 34:44.469
- Bye, sweetheart.
- Good-bye!

34:44.510 --> 34:45.650
Drive safe.

34:49.679 --> 34:51.120
Are you sure you turned the ovens off?

34:51.179 --> 34:53.070
Uh, yeah. Four times.

34:54.719 --> 34:55.520
How's Robert?

34:56.290 --> 34:58.040
Uh, he's fine. He's fine.

34:58.100 --> 34:59.590
They just, uh, changed his medication.

35:00.120 --> 35:00.770
Good.

35:05.850 --> 35:06.790
Wait, wait, wait, wait.

35:06.840 --> 35:08.140
Whoa, whoa, whoa.

35:09.570 --> 35:11.640
Did you mean what you said
about going without you?

35:11.690 --> 35:13.250
To Haiti? Yes, I did.

35:16.040 --> 35:17.430
Look, I was just thinking
about Robert and Kitty

35:17.470 --> 35:20.260
and... and... and how they're
there for each other, you know?

35:20.300 --> 35:22.360
And that... that's what
I want for us, Rebecca.

35:22.860 --> 35:23.740
I know you do.

35:25.500 --> 35:26.330
Me, too.

35:27.370 --> 35:29.430
And you think we can
survive this separation?

35:29.880 --> 35:31.520
Would you be happy any other way?

35:31.890 --> 35:33.190
I know that a year is a long time,

35:33.240 --> 35:34.640
but compared to a lifetime,

35:34.830 --> 35:37.280
- a year is nothing.
- To, I mean, a lifetime?

35:37.500 --> 35:38.960
- Justin...
- Like a real lifetime?

35:39.590 --> 35:40.630
I love you.

35:40.730 --> 35:42.220
I love you, too.

35:48.180 --> 35:50.930
You're listening to
conservative talk radio.

35:51.240 --> 35:53.350
When he was elected president
of the United States...

35:53.410 --> 35:55.720
I've been thinking about
the whole Stanton thing.

35:55.770 --> 35:58.160
Yeah. I think you
should release the tapes.

35:58.220 --> 36:00.960
Reputation was already characterized...

36:01.010 --> 36:01.920
I'm serious.

36:02.690 --> 36:05.210
- We would take a major hit.
- Mm-hmm.

36:05.330 --> 36:07.350
- And we might even lose, but...
- Yeah,

36:07.480 --> 36:09.080
but if we play it safe and wait until

36:09.120 --> 36:11.480
- the election is over, he's still gonna come after me...
- Exactly.

36:11.540 --> 36:13.250
And he's gonna come after me just as hard.

36:16.010 --> 36:18.410
You want to know what
Stanton's big mistake was?

36:20.440 --> 36:21.980
He never should've brought up the wig.

36:24.330 --> 36:26.239
It really pissed me off.

36:26.240 --> 36:27.510
Died in the Civil War.

36:27.511 --> 36:29.630
And the focus on States' rights...

36:30.190 --> 36:30.910
Release 'em.

36:30.970 --> 36:31.690
Let's release 'em.

36:32.120 --> 36:35.610
Through the first quarter
of 2010, but has...

36:39.240 --> 36:40.680
Well, I'm glad you're okay, Saul...

36:41.250 --> 36:42.150
You big drama queen.

36:42.190 --> 36:43.430
That's very funny, Kevin. Th...

36:43.460 --> 36:45.300
Listen, Holly's getting a phone call.

36:45.360 --> 36:47.200
- We'll talk later. Okay?
- Okay. Bye.

36:47.280 --> 36:49.040
- Hello?
- Hey, where are you guys?

36:49.080 --> 36:50.760
We're almost at the Ventura border.

36:50.810 --> 36:52.000
